ADDIS ABABA, Oct. 28 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia registered 472 new COVID-19 cases in the past 24 hours, taking the nationwide tally to 363,712 as of Wednesday evening, the country's health ministry said. The ministry reported 19 new COVID-19 induced deaths and 1,497 more recoveries during the same period, bringing the national death toll to 6,412 and total recoveries to 338,411. Ethiopia, Africa's second-most populous nation, has so far reported the largest number of COVID-19 cases in the East Africa region. Amid a national push for vaccination, Ethiopia has so far administered a total of 4,489,586 COVID-19 vaccine doses, officials said. Ethiopia is among the countries hardest hit by COVID-19 in Africa, following South Africa, Morocco, and Tunisia. Enditem